'''Sonakshi Sinha''' ({{IPA-hns|soːnaːkʂiː sɪnɦaː|pron}}; born 2 June 1987) is an Indian film actress and singer.<ref>{{cite web|author1=Joginder Tuteja|title=Sonakshi Sinha Turns Singer-Rapper|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/hindi/Sonakshi-Sinha-Turns-Singer-Rapper/2015/12/31/article3203720.ece|website=[[The New Indian Express]]|accessdate=3 January 2016|date=31 December 2015}}</ref> After working as a costume designer in her early career, Sinha made her acting debut in the action-drama film ''[[Dabangg]]'' (2010), which won her the [[Filmfare Award for Best Female Debut]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Salman Khan hosts an impromptu birthday bash for Sonakshi Sinha|url=http://www.mid-day.com/articles/salman-hosts-an-impromptu-birthday-bash-for-sonakshi-sinha/16260195|accessdate=12 October 2017|author=Gaurav Dubey|work=[[Mid Day]]}}</ref> 

Sinha has played the romantic interest of the male protagonists in several top-grossing action-dramas, including ''[[Rowdy Rathore]]'' (2012), ''[[Son of Sardaar]]'' (2012), ''[[Dabangg 2]]'' (2012) and ''[[Holiday: A Soldier Is Never Off Duty]]'' (2014), though she was criticized for taking up roles that offered her limited scope. She gained critical acclaim for her portrayal of a woman suffering from tuberculosis in the romantic drama ''[[Lootera]]'' (2013), for which she received a nomination for the [[Filmfare Award for Best Actress]].<ref name="The Times of India 2014">{{cite news|title=Sonakshi Sinha: Year since 'Lootera', appreciation hasn't stopped|work=The Times of India|date=5 July 2014|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Sonakshi-Sinha-Year-since-Lootera-appreciation-hasnt-stopped/articleshow/37838144.cms|agency=IANS|accessdate=28 November 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714174734/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Sonakshi-Sinha-Year-since-Lootera-appreciation-hasnt-stopped/articleshow/37838144.cms|archivedate=14 July 2014|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/shatrughan-sinha-breaks-down-after-watching-daughter-sonakshi-in-lootera/1139060/|title=Shatrughan Sinha breaks down after watching daughter Sonakshi in Lootera|work=Indian Express|accessdate=12 October 2017}}</ref><ref>http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/features/no-one-doubted-capacity-actor-past-well-sonakshi-sinha-akira-appreciation/</ref> She followed this initial success by starring in a series of commercial failures, with the exception of ''[[Mission Mangal]]'' (2019), in which she had a supporting role.<ref>{{cite web|title=Sonakshi Sinha|url=https://boxofficeindia.com/actor.php?actorid=65|accessdate=8 March 2018|website=[[Box Office India]]}}</ref>

In addition to acting in films, Sinha has sung a small part in the [[Imran Khan (singer)|Imran Khan]] song "Let's Celebrate" in her film ''[[Tevar]]'' (2015). She has also sung the single "[[Aaj Mood Ishqholic Hai|Aaj Mood Isqholic Hai]]" and sung in a total of four of her films.

==Early life==
Sinha was born on 2 June 1987 in [[Patna]], [[Bihar]],<ref name="DOB"/> to film actors [[Shatrughan Sinha]] and [[Poonam Sinha]] (née Chandiramani). Her father belongs to a [[Biharis|Bihari]] [[Kayastha]] family while her mother hails from a [[Sindhi Hindus|Sindhi Hindu]] family.<ref>{{cite news |author=Pradhan S. Bharati |title=It's work first for Sonakshi |url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/1120610/jsp/7days/story_15591857.jsp |work=[[The Telegraph (Kolkata)]] |date=12 June 2012 |accessdate=30 October 2019}}</ref> Her father served as a [[Member of Parliament]] of the [[Bharatiya Janata Party]],<ref name="DOB">{{cite news|url=http://zeenews.india.com/entertainment/celebrity/shotgun-junior-sonakshi-sinha-turns-26_135886.html|title='Shotgun Junior' Sonakshi Sinha turns 26!|work=Zee News|accessdate=12 October 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://m.ndtv.com/photos/entertainment/sonakshi-sinha-s-birthday-with-fans-8785/slide/2|title=Sonakshi Sinhas birthday with fans|publisher=NDTV|accessdate=3 October 2014}}</ref> before he switched to the [[Indian National Congress]] in 2019. Sinha is the youngest of three children {{endash}} she has two (twin) brothers, [[Luv Sinha]] and Kush Sinha. She did her schooling at Arya Vidya Mandir and later graduated in fashion designing from Premlila Vithaldas Polytechnic of [[SNDT Women's University|Shreemati Nathibai Damodar Thackersey Women's University]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Just How educated are our Bollywood heroines?|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-just-how-educated-are-bollywood-heroines/20120118.htm#11|website=[[Rediff.com]]|accessdate=12 October 2017|date=18 January 2012}}</ref>

==Career==

===Debut and breakthrough (2010–14)===
Sinha started her career as a costume designer, designing the costumes for films such as ''Mera Dil Leke Dekho'' in 2005.<ref>{{cite web|title=Who is Sonakshi Sinha?|url=http://www.ndtv.com/article/people/who-is-sonakshi-sinha-229078|publisher=NDTV|accessdate=12 July 2013|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131004234807/http://www.ndtv.com/article/people/who-is-sonakshi-sinha-229078|archivedate=4 October 2013|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>
She made her acting debut in the 2010 film ''[[Dabangg]]'', in which she starred opposite [[Salman Khan]]. It went on to become the [[List of Bollywood films of 2012|highest-grossing film of 2010]] and ultimately emerged as an all-time blockbuster.<ref>{{cite web|title=Top Lifetime Grossers 2010–2019 (Figures in Ind Rs)|url=http://boxofficeindia.com/showProd.php?itemCat=317&catName=MjAxMC0yMDE5|publisher=Box Office India|accessdate=12 July 2013|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130621153241/http://boxofficeindia.com/showProd.php?itemCat=317&catName=MjAxMC0yMDE5|archivedate=21 June 2013|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title='Dabangg' 17th on list of highest grossers|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/Dabangg-17th-on-list-of-highest-grossers/articleshow/6633161.cms|publisher=Times of India|accessdate=12 October 2017|date=27 September 2010}}</ref> Sinha had to lose 3&nbsp;kg in preparation for the role as a village girl.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://archive.mid-day.com/entertainment/2009/oct/291009-sonakshi-sinha-dabangg.htm|title=Sonakshi Sinha lost 30 kgs [sic] for her debut film Dabangg|work=[[MiD DAY]]|accessdate=12 October 2017|date=29 October 2009|author=Tushar Doshi}}</ref> Her performance was well received, with noted critic [[Taran Adarsh]] noting that "Sonakshi Sinha looks fresh, acts confidently and pairs off very well with Salman. Most importantly, she delivers the right expressions and is not overpowered by the galaxy of stars in the cast."<ref>{{cite web|author=[[Taran Adarsh]]|title=Dabangg (2010) Movie Review|date=8 September 2010|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movie/dabangg/critic-review/|publisher=Bollywood Hungama|accessdate=12 October 2017}}</ref> Although Sinha had no film releases in 2011, she won awards for her debut. This included the [[Filmfare Award]] as well as the [[IIFA Awards]] among many others.

Sinha had four releases in 2012, her first being [[Prabhu Deva]]'s ''[[Rowdy Rathore]]'', opposite [[Akshay Kumar]]. The film opened to mixed reviews from critics,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/039rowdy-rathore039-movie-review-roundup-mixed-reaction-from-critics-348037|title='Rowdy Rathore' Movie Review Roundup: Mixed Reaction From Critics – International Business Times |publisher=Ibtimes.co.in|date=2 June 2012|accessdate=12 October 2017}}</ref> although it had a strong opening at the box office,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://boxofficeindia.com/boxdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=4497&nCat=|title=Rowdy Rathore Bumper Opening In Single Screens Good At Multiplexes|publisher=Box Office India|date=26 May 2012|accessdate=21 July 2012|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120626144856/http://boxofficeindia.com/boxdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=4497&nCat=|archivedate=26 June 2012|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref> collecting approx. {{INRConvert|150.6|m}} on the first day and eventually became a blockbuster.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://boxofficeindia.com/boxnewsdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=4501&nCat=|title=Rowdy Rathore First Day Territorial Breakdown|publisher=Box Office India|date=2 June 2012|accessdate=21 July 2012|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120707081148/http://boxofficeindia.com/boxnewsdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=4501&nCat=|archivedate=7 July 2012|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Despite this, critic [[Rajeev Masand]] criticized her ornamental role and wrote that Sinha "seems to exist in this film only to have her midriff repeatedly pinched by Akshay Kumar."<ref>{{cite news|url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/masand-rowdy-rathore-is-a-mindless-film/263714-47-84.html|title=Masand: 'Rowdy Rathore' is a mindless film|author=[[Rajeev Masand]]|work=IBNLive|accessdate=3 October 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141008073935/http://ibnlive.in.com/news/masand-rowdy-rathore-is-a-mindless-film/263714-47-84.html|archivedate=8 October 2014|publisher=CNN-IBN|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Her next film, [[Shirish Kunder]]'s ''[[Joker (2012 film)|Joker]]'', also opposite Akshay Kumar, proved to be a commercial disaster at the box office and received overwhelmingly negative reviews.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://entertainment.oneindia.in/bollywood/features/2012/akshay-kumar-joker-reviews-ratings-film-critics-098969.html|title=Akshay Kumar's Joker gets negative reviews from film critics|accessdate=12 October 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://entertainment.oneindia.in/bollywood/box-office/2012/akshay-joker-first-weekend-collection-box-office-099026.html|title=Akshay Kumar's Joker tanks at Box Office|accessdate=12 October 2017}}</ref> [[File:Sonakshi Sinha at the DVD launch of 'Rowdy Rathore'.jpg|thumb|upright|Sinha at DVD launch of ''[[Rowdy Rathore]]'' in 2012|alt=]] Her third film, [[Ashwni Dhir]]'s ''[[Son of Sardar]]'', opposite [[Ajay Devgn]], was poorly received by the critics, but proved to be an economic success. Critic Saibal Chatterjee from [[NDTV]] noted that Sinha "endeavours to be pretty and dainty amid all the madness."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://movies.ndtv.com/movie-reviews/movie-review-son-of-sardaar-760|title=Movie review: Son Of Sardaar|work=NDTVMovies.com|accessdate=12 October 2017}}</ref> [[Arbaaz Khan]]'s ''[[Dabangg 2]]'', the sequel to her immensely successful debut garnered little praise from critics, though it proved to be a major financial success.<ref name="Kumar 2013">{{cite news|author=Raksha Kumar|title=What Made 'Dabangg 2' a Hit?|website=India Ink|date=24 January 2013|publisher=New York Times|url=http://india.blogs.nytimes.com/2013/01/24/why-was-salman-khans-dabangg-2-a-hit-when-it-bombed-with-critics/|accessdate=12 October 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Ajay Devgn's Son of Sardar gets mixed reviews from critics!|url=http://entertainment.oneindia.in/bollywood/reviews/2012/son-of-sardar-critics-review-101147.html|accessdate=12 October 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Dabangg 2 Emerges Blockbuster|url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/boxdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=5244&nCat=|accessdate=5 February 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=‘Dabangg 2' Review Roundup: Action, Comedy Gets Mixed Reviews From Critics|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/articles/417786/20121222/dabangg-2-review-roundup-action-comedy-gets.htm|accessdate=5 February 2013}}</ref> Sinha also [[Dubbing (filmmaking)|dubbed]] for the voice of Tooth in the Hindi version of ''[[Rise of the Guardians]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://movies.ndtv.com/bollywood/sonakshi-sinha-likely-to-dub-for-hindi-i-rise-of-the-guardians-i-291981 |title=Sonakshi Sinha likely to dub for Hindi Rise of the Guardians? |publisher=NDTV.com |date=13 November 2012 |accessdate=31 July 2013}}</ref>

Sinha's first film of 2013 was [[Vikramaditya Motwane]]'s period romance-drama ''[[Lootera]]'', placing her opposite [[Ranveer Singh]]. Despite receiving a lukewarm response at the box office,<ref>{{cite news|title=Bhaag Milkha Bhaag Picks Up Strongly Lootera Is Poor|url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/boxdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=5854&nCat=|publisher=Box Office India|accessdate=28 July 2013|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130716191708/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/boxdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=5854&nCat=|archivedate=16 July 2013|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref> the film and Sinha gathered praise,<ref>{{cite news|title=Lootera: a slow pace romantic saga worth watching, say critics|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/lootera-a-slow-pace-romantic-saga-worth-watching-say-critics/story-moWTXgmxMLdRSaHF2lHlYN.html|accessdate=12 October 2017|newspaper=Hindustan Times|date=5 July 2013}}</ref> with Sinha's portrayal of Pakhi, a Bengali girl who is dying of [[tuberculosis]], receiving universal acclaim from critics. Sarita Tanwar notes that "the star of the film is undoubtedly Sonakshi Sinha [who gives] a mature and refined performance. She lives the character body and soul."<ref>{{cite web|author=Sarita Tanwar|title=Movie Review: Lootera charms you and slowly draws you into its lost world|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-movie-review-lootera-charms-you-and-slowly-draws-you-into-its-lost-world-1857364|publisher=DNA India|date=5 July 2013|accessdate=12 October 2017}}</ref> Raja Sen agrees, saying that "Sonakshi Sinha plays Pakhi beautifully, creating a character who is immaculately wide-eyed and possesses casual, yet unmistakable, grace. It is a performance that starts off dreamily soft and turns harder, and she does well-etched dialogue justice like few actresses can. There's a discernible vulnerability to Pakhi throughout the film, and Sinha brings out this fragility perfectly without ever overplaying it."<ref>{{cite web|author=Raja Sen|title=Review: Lootera is an absolute masterpiece|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/review-lootera-is-an-absolute-masterpiece/20130704.htm|website=Rediff.com|accessdate=12 October 2017}}</ref>

Sinha appeared in [[Milan Luthria]]'s [[crime film|crime]] [[romance film]] ''[[Once Upon a Time in Mumbai Dobaara!]]'', the sequel to ''[[Once Upon a Time in Mumbaai]]'', in which she was paired with [[Akshay Kumar]] again, as well as [[Imran Khan (Bollywood actor)|Imran Khan]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Sonakshi Sinha has a new name in Once Upon A Time In Mumbaai Again|url=http://movies.ndtv.com/bollywood/sonakshi-sinha-has-a-new-name-in-once-upon-a-time-in-mumbaai-again-383280|date=24 June 2013|publisher=NDTV|accessdate=12 October 2017}}</ref> The movie was a commercial disappointment and critic Mohar Basu labeled her "a chatterbox replete with idioticity which the director frames as naiveness."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.koimoi.com/reviews/once-upon-ay-time-in-dobaara-review/|title=Bollywood News - Reviews - Bollywood Gossip - Box Office - Photos - Videos Bollywood - Koimoi.com|work=Koimoi|accessdate=3 October 2014}} {{Dead link|date=October 2017}}</ref> She then appeared in [[Tigmanshu Dhulia]]'s ''[[Bullett Raja]]'' opposite [[Saif Ali Khan]], a box office flop. Her final release of the year was Prabhu Deva's ''[[R... Rajkumar]]'' opposite [[Shahid Kapoor]]. A moderate commercial success, the film and her performance received negative reviews. [[Taran Adarsh]] labeled her "repetitive" and noted that she needed to "reinvent herself."<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movie/r-rajkumar/critic-review/|author=Taran Adarsh|title=R... Rajkumar|publisher=Bollywood Hungama|date=6 December 2013|accessdate=12 October 2017}}</ref>

In 2014, after providing her voice for the voice of Jewel in the Hindi-dubbed ''[[Rio 2]]'',<ref name="NDTVMovies.com 2014">{{cite web |title=Sonakshi Sinha sings for the first time in Hindi Rio 2|publisher=NDTV|date=13 March 2014|url=http://movies.ndtv.com/bollywood/sonakshi-sinha-sings-for-the-first-time-in-hindi-rio-2-637963|accessdate=12 October 2017}}</ref>  Sinha was seen in [[A.R. Murugadoss]]'s action thriller ''[[Holiday: A Soldier Is Never Off Duty]]'', a remake of the director's Tamil film ''[[Thuppakki]]''.<ref>{{cite news|title=Akshay Kumar and Sonakshi Sinha's new movie 'Holiday' trailer releases |url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/akshay-kumar-and-sonakshi-sinha-s-new-movie-holiday-trailer-releases-1961456|date=12 February 2014|work=DNA|accessdate=12 October 2017}}</ref> Starring opposite Akshay Kumar, Sinha appeared as a boxer. It received mixed-to-positive reviews from critics and emerged as a box office hit.<ref>{{cite news|title=Review Round Up: Cheap Thrills Make ‘Holiday’ Worth Watching|url=https://blogs.wsj.com/indiarealtime/2014/06/06/review-round-up-cheap-thrills-make-holiday-worth-watching/|accessdate=12 October 2017|work=The Wall Street Journal|date=6 June 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author=Jyoti Sharma Bawa|title=Akshay Kumar's Holiday one of the biggest hits of 2014|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/akshay-kumar-s-holiday-one-of-the-biggest-hits-of-2014/story-8nUbklD17s5OvaQ0iqRkXL.html|accessdate=12 October 2017|work=Hindustan Times|date=11 June 2014}}</ref> Jyoti Sharma Bawa said of Sinha's portrayal: "Sonakshi has nothing to do much in the film and overacts in places. For an actor who has already proved her mettle in the acting department, this definitely is a downer."<ref>{{cite news|author=Jyoti Sharma Bawa|title=Movie review: Akshay impresses in Holiday's action sequences|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/movie-reviews/movie-review-akshay-impresses-in-holiday-s-action-sequences/story-4LbXNLcseTtn87ehBoqTRI.html|accessdate=12 October 2017|work=Hindustan Times|date=5 June 2014}}</ref> Sinha appeared in a music video with [[Yo Yo Honey Singh]] titled ''Superstar''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indtoday.com/sonakshi-sinha-and-honey-singh-to-dance-together/|title=Sonakshi Sinha and Honey Singh to dance together|work=indtoday.com|accessdate=3 October 2014|archivedate=6 October 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006130255/http://www.indtoday.com/sonakshi-sinha-and-honey-singh-to-dance-together/|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref> In July, Sinha jointly bought a team in the [[World Kabaddi League]].<ref name="India Today 2014">{{cite news|title=Sonakshi Sinha co-owns team in World Kabaddi League : Celebrities, News|work=India Today|date=16 July 2014|url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/sonakshi-sinha-co-owns-team-in-world-kabaddi-league/1/372689.html|agency=PTI|place=[[Mumbai]]|accessdate=12 October 2017}}</ref> Her second release of 2014 was Prabhu Deva's ''[[Action Jackson (2014 film)|Action Jackson]]'', with [[Ajay Devgan|Ajay Devgn]] and [[Yami Gautam]]. She made her [[Tamil cinema]] debut opposite [[Rajinikanth]] in [[KS Ravikumar]]'s ''[[Lingaa]]'', which was her final release in 2014.

=== Career fluctuations (2015–present) ===
In 2015, she appeared in [[Boney Kapoor]]'s remake of ''[[Okkadu]]'', titled ''[[Tevar]]'', opposite [[Arjun Kapoor]].<ref name="upcoming1">{{cite news|url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/ajay-devgn-sonakshi-sinha-to-star-in-prabhu-devas-next/1118206/|title=Ajay Devgn, Sonakshi Sinha to star in Prabhu Deva's next|publisher=|accessdate=3 October 2014}}</ref><ref name="upcoming2">{{cite news|author=Harshada Rege|title=Sonakshi Sinha and Arjun Kapoor set to appear in a film by the guys behind Google ad film, Reunion|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-sonakshi-sinha-and-arjun-kapoor-set-to-appear-in-a-film-by-the-guys-behind-google-ad-film-reunion-1921283|accessdate=12 October 2017|newspaper=Daily News And Analysis|date=19 November 2013}}</ref><ref name="upcoming3">{{cite news|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/rajinikanth-fascinated-by-sonakshi-sinhas-work-in-tamil-debut-film-lingaa/|title=Rajinikanth fascinated by Sonakshi Sinha’s work in Tamil debut film ‘Lingaa’|work=[[The Indian Express]]|date=12 May 2014|accessdate=12 October 2017}}</ref> In his review, Rajeev Masand wrote: "Sonakshi Sinha, playing another simpering damsel in another South remake, once again has nothing to do. She appears content showing up for a few dance numbers, and waiting around for a man to save her."<ref>{{cite web|last=Masand|first=Rajeev|url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/tevar-review-its-an-exhausting-film/522111-47-84.html|title='Tevar' review: It's so long film that gives a throbbing headache|publisher=CNN-IBN|date=10 January 2015|accessdate=17 January 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150112225600/http://ibnlive.in.com/news/tevar-review-its-an-exhausting-film/522111-47-84.html|archivedate=12 January 2015|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref> ''Tevar'' underperformed at the box office and was one of the biggest flops of the year.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rediff.com/movies/report/the-top-10-flops-of-2015/20151221.htm|title=The Top 10 FLOPS of 2015|website=Rediff|access-date=2019-04-05}}</ref>
[[File:Sonakhi launch song.jpg|thumb|Sinha during a song launching event for ''[[Force 2]]'', in 2016|alt=]]
Sonakshi released her debut single "[[Aaj Mood Ishqholic Hai]]", in collaboration with [[Meet Bros]] on 23 December 2015.<ref>{{cite news|author=Shreya Thakur|title=Sonakshi Sinha’s badass look in Desi Kalakaar or boho-chic in Aaj Mood Hai Ishqoholic –vote now!|url=http://www.bollywoodlife.com/news-gossip/sonakshi-sinhas-badass-look-in-desi-kalakaar-or-boho-chic-in-aaj-mood-hai-ishqoholic-vote-now/|website=Bollywood Life|accessdate=12 October 2017|date=23 December 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://m.ibtimes.co.in/sonakshi-sinha-turns-singer-records-her-first-single-655569|title=Sonakshi Sinha turns singer; records her first single|work=[[International Business Times]]|date=19 November 2015|accessdate=12 October 2017}}</ref>

In 2016, Sinha starred in the remake of the 2011 Tamil film ''[[Mouna Guru]]'', entitled ''[[Akira (2016 Hindi film)|Akira]]'', an action-drama from director [[AR Murugadoss]], in which she played an aggressive college student. ''Akira'' had taken the best start at the box office amongst all female-centric releases of 2016.<ref>https://www.koimoi.com/box-office/sonakshi-sinhas-akira-opens-better-than-neerja-sarbjit-and-happy-bhag-jayegi/</ref> The film had initial recovery of 15.5 crore, and the film made over 33+ crore on box office, becoming an average grosser.<ref>https://www.koimoi.com/box-office/box-office-economics-of-akira-recovers-more-than-50-of-its-investment-already/</ref> Then, she appeared in [[Abhinay Deo]]'s action-thriller ''[[Force 2]]'', opposite [[John Abraham (actor)|John Abraham]].<ref name="akira">{{cite news|title=Sonakshi Sinha on sets of her action thriller 'Akira'|url=http://www.mid-day.com/articles/sonakshi-sinha-on-sets-of-her-action-thriller-akira/16072193|work=[[Mid Day]]|date=18 March 2015|accessdate=12 October 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=A.R. Murugadoss' next starring Sonakshi Sinha titled Akira|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/5303367/A.R.-Murugadoss-next-starring-Sonakshi-Sinha-titled-Akira|accessdate=12 October 2017|date=21 April 2015|publisher=Bollywood Hungama}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Akira to Force 2: Sonakshi has her hands full|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/akira-to-force-2-sonakshi-sinha-has-her-hands-full/story-gTE4EPKSgnPyD3fbdkfKPP.html|accessdate=12 October 2017|date=1 July 2016|work=Hindustan Times|author=Jigar Shah}}</ref> The film made on a low budget, grossed over 58.75 crore and was declared an average grosser.<ref>https://www.koimoi.com/box-office/force-2-2nd-week-box-office-collections/</ref> Though Sinha's character was labeled as a unformed agent, her performance received some acclaim. ''Bollywood Life'' reviewed her performance as "Sonakshi Sinha is believable in action scenes she got and ably supports John."<ref>https://www.bollywoodlife.com/news-gossip/force-2-movie-review-the-john-abraham-sonakshi-sinha-starrer-is-a-perfect-blend-of-an-intelligent-plot-and-high-octane-action-scenes/</ref>

In 2017, she was seen in Sunhil Sippy's comedy film ''[[Noor (film)|Noor]]'' based on [[Saba Imtiaz]]'s novel ''[[Karachi, You're Killing Me!]]''. She featured in the titular role of Noor alongside [[Kanan Gill]], [[Shibani Dandekar]] and [[Purab Kohli]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Today's headlines are tomorrow's garbage: Sonakshi|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/life-style/people/Todays-headlines-are-tomorrows-garbage-Sonakshi/articleshow/53074037.cms|accessdate=12 October 2017|work=Times Of India|author=Natasha Coutinho|date=6 July 2016}}</ref> Her performance received major acclaim, with one reviewer writing that "Sonakshi Sinha pulls off her character without appearing to try too hard."<ref>https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/noor-movie-review-sonakshi-sinhas-film-is-flawed-but-its-not-akira-style-fake-woman-centricity-3396604.html</ref> ''Hindustan Times'' wrote that "Sonakshi looks quite convincing with the grimaces, pouts, eye rolls, scowls and goofy grins - displaying an amusing dorkiness. Even when her character turns serious, Sonakshi displays her prowess and aces the grim looks."<ref>https://www.khaleejtimes.com/citytimes/bollywood/noor-movie-review-sonakshi-shines-but</ref> Commercially, the film flopped.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rediff.com/movies/report/bollywoods-biggest-flops-of-2017-so-far/20170628.htm|title=Bollywood's BIGGEST FLOPS of 2017 so far|website=Rediff|access-date=2019-04-04}}</ref> Her last film release in the year was Abhay Chopra's [[Ittefaq (2017 film)|''Ittefaq'']], a remake of the 1969 murder mystery [[Ittefaq (1969 film)|''Ittefaq'']], opposite [[Sidharth Malhotra]], and [[Akshay Khanna]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/box-office/ittefaq-box-office-collection-day-8-the-sonakshi-sinha-sidharth-malhotra-starrer-lows-down-further-on-second-friday/articleshow/61606317.cms|title=‘Ittefaq’ box-office collection Day 8: The Sonakshi Sinha-Sidharth Malhotra starrer lows down further on second Friday - Times of India|website=The Times of India|language=en}}</ref> The film was a moderate box-office success.<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|url=https://www.india.com/showbiz/will-the-success-of-ittefaq-resurrect-sidharth-malhotras-career-graph-2609656/|title=Will Ittefaq's Success Resurrect Sidharth Malhotra's Career Graph?|last=Abbasi|first=Mehfooz|date=2017-11-08|website=India.com|language=en|access-date=2019-10-31}}</ref><ref name=":2">{{Cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/entertainment/ittefaq-box-office-collection-day-3-sonakshi-sinha-and-sidharth-malhotras-film-shows-steady-growth-w-1771654|title=Ittefaq Box Office Collection Day 3: Sonakshi Sinha And Sidharth Malhotra's Film Shows 'Steady Growth' With Over Rs 15 Crore|website=NDTV.com|access-date=2019-10-31}}</ref> It was a commercial failure.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://boxofficeindia.com/movie.php?movieid=3643|title=Ittefaq|website=Box Office India|accessdate=31 October 2019}}</ref>

In March 2017, Sinha announced that she was working on a new single. Despite speculation she might perform as the opening act for Canadian singer [[Justin Bieber]]'s [[Purpose World Tour]] concert at the [[DY Patil Stadium]] in [[Mumbai]] on 10 May, <ref>{{cite news|title=Sonakshi Sinha to perform at Bieber's Mumbai gig|url=https://www.thenews.com.pk/latest/192242-Sonakshi-Sinha-to-perform-at-Biebers-Mumbai-gig|accessdate=12 October 2017|work=[[The News International]]|date=14 March 2017}}</ref> her performance did not occur.<ref>''Indo Asian News Service'', "Not Performing at Justin Bieber Concert in India" (5 June 2017): https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/not-performing-at-justin-bieber-concert-in-india-sonakshi-sinha/story-HotDBgBV9eCOTOAQjQPKoO.html</ref>

In 2018, she was seen in comedy spoof film [[Welcome to New York (2018 film)|''Welcome to New York'']], with an ensemble cast including [[Diljit Dosanjh]], [[Karan Johar]], and others. The film was shot in IIFA Awards 2017 and was the first film to be based on an award show.<ref>http://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/golmaal-in-new-york-sonakshi-sinha-diljit-dosanjhs-upcoming-film-gets-a-name-4147783.html</ref> The film received overwhelming negative reviews and Sinha's appearance in the film was particularly criticized, with Rajeev Masand of [[News 18]] saying that <nowiki>''</nowiki>Not very funny, unfortunately, is Sonakshi Sinha, who comes off exaggerated and out-of-step even in a film of such ridiculously low standards. She spends the bulk of her time on screen contorting her face like [[Jim Carrey]], but with none of the same results.<nowiki>''</nowiki><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.news18.com/news/movies/welcome-to-new-york-review-diljit-dosanjh-starrer-isnt-just-a-terrible-film-but-a-depressing-one-1670351.html|title=Welcome to New York Review: Diljit Dosanjh-Starrer Isn't Just A Terrible Film But A Depressing One|website=News18}}</ref> The film was also a box-office bomb, earning only Rs. 75 lakh on its first day.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/box-office-collection/welcome-to-new-york-box-office-collection-day-1-this-diljit-dosanjh-and-sonakshi-sinha-film-5075374/|title=Welcome to New York box office collection day 1: This Diljit Dosanjh and Sonakshi Sinha film earns Rs 75 lakh|date=2018-02-24|website=The Indian Express|language=en-IN}}</ref> The same year, Sinha appeared in female-oriented comedy film ''[[Happy Phirr Bhag Jayegi]]'' along with [[Diana Penty]] in the eponymous character. The film was released on 24 August 2018.<ref>http://www.magtheweekly.com/detail/388-sonakshi-to-star-in-happy-bhaag-jayegi-returns</ref> As with her previous release, ''Happy Phirr Bhag Jayegi'' was a commercial disappointment.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/entertainment/happy-phirr-bhag-jayegi-box-office-collection-day-7-sonakshi-sinhas-film-witnesses-a-noticeable-decl-1909364|title=Happy Phirr Bhag Jayegi Box Office Collection Day 7: Sonakshi Sinha's Film Witnesses A 'Noticeable Decline,' Earns Rs 18.11 Crore|website=NDTV.com|access-date=2019-05-03}}</ref> Then, she made a special appearance in a song of ''[[Yamla Pagla Deewana Phir Se]]''. 

In 2019, she performed in a song <nowiki>''Mungda''</nowiki> in comedy film ''[[Total Dhamaal]].''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/bollywood/ajay-devgn-sonakshi-sinha-recreate-iconic-track-mungda-total-dhamaal/|title=Ajay Devgn and Sonakshi Sinha to recreate the iconic track ‘Mungda’ for Total Dhamaal - Bollywood Hungama|last=Hungama|first=Bollywood|date=2018-08-23|language=en}}</ref> She next starred in the period romance film ''[[Kalank]]'' with an ensemble cast including [[Aditya Roy Kapur]], [[Sanjay Dutt]], [[Madhuri Dixit]], [[Alia Bhatt]] and [[Varun Dhawan]]. The film failed to perform well commercially.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.india.com/showbiz/bollywood-news-sonakshi-sinha-speaks-on-kalanks-failure-at-box-office-says-its-not-in-my-hands-3638736/|title=Sonakshi Sinha Speaks on Kalank's Failure at Box Office, Says 'It's Not in my Hands'|last=Desk|first=India com Entertainment|date=2019-04-22|website=India.com|language=en|access-date=2019-05-03}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pinkvilla.com/entertainment/news/sonakshi-sinha-kalanks-dismal-box-office-collection-it-bad-luck-not-my-control-447718|title=Sonakshi Sinha on Kalank's dismal box office collection: It is bad luck, not in my control|website=PINKVILLA|language=en|access-date=2019-05-03}}</ref>

[[File:Sonakshi Sinha at the trailer launch of her film 'Mission Mangal'.jpg|thumb|Sinha in 2019, promoting ''[[Mission Mangal]]''|alt=]]In 2019, Sinha was cast in drama film ''[[Mission Mangal]]'', which featured an ensemble cast, including Akshay Kumar, [[Vidya Balan]] and [[Taapsee Pannu]]. The project began filming in 2018,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/photo-features/movies-to-look-forward-to/mission-mangal-akshay-kumar-reveals-the-star-cast-of-his-film/photostory/66513144.cms|title='Mission Mangal': Akshay Kumar reveals the star cast of his film - Movies to look forward to|website=The Times of India|access-date=2019-10-29}}</ref> and was directed by Jagan Shakti. The film was a massive commercial success at the box-office,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bollywoodhungama.com/box-office-collections/worldwide/|title=Worldwide Highest Grossing Bollywood Movies on 2019 - Bollywood Hungama|last=Hungama|first=Bollywood|language=en|access-date=2019-10-29}}</ref> grossing over 200 crore on a budget of 30 crore,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/sonakshi-sinha-on-mission-mangal-success-well-made-films-with-patriotic-spirit-liked-by-people/articleshow/71032562.cms |title=Sonakshi Sinha on 'Mission Mangal' success: Well-made films with patriotic spirit liked by people |website=The Times of India |access-date=2019-10-31}}</ref> and received positive reviews from critics.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/mission-mangal-movie-review-rating-early-response-turns-out-be-positive-803555|title=Mission Mangal movie review and rating: Critics verdict on Akshay Kumar starrer out|last=Sarkar|first=Suparno|date=2019-08-14|website=International Business Times, India Edition|language=english|access-date=2019-10-29}}</ref> She is appearing alongside [[Ajay Devgn]], Sanjay Dutt and [[Parineeti Chopra]] in war drama film ''[[Bhuj: The Pride of India]].''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/bhuj-the-pride-of-india-sanjay-dutt-sonakshi-sinha-rana-daggubati-parineeti-chopra-and-ammy-virk-join-the-ajay-devgn-starrer/articleshow/68493083.cms|title=‘Bhuj: The Pride of India’: Sanjay Dutt, Sonakshi Sinha, Rana Daggubati, Parineeti Chopra and Ammy Virk join the Ajay Devgn starrer - Times of India|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=2019-03-22}}</ref> After that, she will reprise her role in ''[[Dabangg 3]]'' opposite [[Salman Khan]], which will be directed by [[Prabhu Deva]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/dabangg-3-shoot-will-start-by-middle-of-next-year-reveals-arbaaz-khan-4907193/|title=Dabangg 3 shoot will start by middle of next year, reveals Arbaaz Khan|date=2017-10-26|website=The Indian Express|language=en-IN}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/photo-features/dabangg-to-kick-salman-khans-upcoming-sequels/dabangg-3-sonakshi-sinha-is-back-in-her-rajjo-avatar-as-she-kick-starts-shooting-for-the-film/photostory/68717590.cms|title=‘Dabangg 3’: Sonakshi Sinha is back in her ‘Rajjo’ avatar as she kick-starts shooting for the film - Dabangg to Kick: Salman Khan's upcoming sequels|website=The Times of India|access-date=2019-04-05}}</ref>

=== KBC Controversy ===
On 21 September 2019, after failing to answer a question in show Kaun Banega Crorepati 11, she was promptly [[Trolling|trolled]] on Twitter.<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/magazines/panache/sonakshi-sinha-gets-trolled-for-failing-to-answer-kbc-question-actor-tweets/articleshow/71232838.cms|title=Sonakshi Sinha trolled for failing to answer 'KBC' question; actor tweets|date=2019-09-21|work=The Economic Times|access-date=2019-09-22}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/celebrities/story/sonakshi-sinha-kisses-trolls-goodbye-and-burns-up-maldives-in-swimsuit-see-pic-1601644-2019-09-21|title=Sonakshi Sinha kisses trolls goodbye and burns up Maldives in swimsuit. See pic|newspaper=India Today|language=en|access-date=2019-09-22|agency=Ist}}</ref> During the 25th episode of KBC 11, the show’s actor-host [[Amitabh Bachchan]] asked Sonakshi, who shared the hot-seat with Rajasthani artisan [[Ruma Devi]], the question "According to Ramayana, Hanuman fetched the Sanjeevani herb for whom?" Sonakshi failed to answer the question, which led to widespread trolling of her on the micro-blogging site [[Twitter]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/big-bs-dig-at-sonakshi-sinha-over-kbc-gaffe/article29476411.ece|title=Amitabh Bachchan bemused at Sonakshi Sinha over ‘KBC’ gaffe|last=Ians|date=2019-09-21|work=The Hindu|access-date=2019-09-22|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref><ref name=":0" /> #YoSonakshiSoDumb was trending on the Twitter during the time, as well as Amitabh Bachchan also made fun of her because of lack of general knowledge.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/kbc11-yosonakshisodumb-trends-as-actress-sonakshi-sinha-fails-to-answer-a-question-on-ramayana/articleshow/71231072.cms|title=KBC11: #YoSonakshiSoDumb trends as actress Sonakshi Sinha fails to answer a question on Ramayana - Times of India|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=2019-09-22}}</ref> In the response, she sarcastically accepted that she doesn't have knowledge of [[Pythagoras Theorem|Phythagoras Theorem]], Mughal Chronological order and concluded with her love for memes in the response to trolling.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/entertainment/kaun-banega-crorepati-11-sonakshi-sinha-trolled-for-not-knowing-the-answer-to-this-ramayana-question-2104740|title='I Love Memes': Sonakshi Sinha's Response To Those Who Trolled Her For Kaun Banega Crorepati Oopsie|website=NDTV.com|access-date=2019-09-22}}</ref>

== Philanthropy ==
Sinha is a professed animal lover, and she had posed for a [[PETA]] campaign advocating the adoption and sterilization of dogs and cats.<ref>{{cite news|agency=IANS|title=Sonakshi Sinha join forces with PETA, appeals fans to adopt cats, dogs|url=http://www.news18.com/news/india/sonakshi-sinha-join-forces-with-peta-appeals-fans-to-adopt-cats-dogs-630896.html|publisher=News18|accessdate=12 October 2017}}</ref> She has starred in a one-minute video PSA, urging everyone to adopt animals and have them sterilised. She has been quoted saying: "Breeders, pet stores and people who don't sterilize their animals are responsible for all the animals who end up homeless. Every time someone buys a dog or cat from a breeder or pet store, a homeless animal roaming the streets or waiting in an animal shelter loses a chance at a home and a good life."<ref>{{cite web|title=Sonakshi Sinha Stars in New PETA Ad|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/features/sonakshi-sinha-stars-in-new-peta-ad/|publisher=Bollywood Hungama|accessdate=12 October 2017}}</ref> She also promotes breaking the steroptypes of typical body size.<ref>https://www.google.ca/search?q=sonakshi+sinha+rise+above+looks&rlz=1CADEAC_enCA760CA760&tbm=isch&source=iu&ictx=1&fir=3kU2UXDWth4v3M%253A%252CQROC8Euc4AJpfM%252C_&usg=__7R94PUdI-XI_nM22XWKdFiTa9Dw%3D&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjy3uKo25_cAhXXBjQIHcVhAXcQ9QEIKzAB#imgrc=3kU2UXDWth4v3M:</ref><ref>https://indianexpress.com/article/lifestyle/fitness/i-work-towards-breaking-patterns-of-my-body-sonakshi-sinha-5186800/</ref>

